piece of woke duplicity.\\\"\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So we have a group of drag queens cavorting in a sort of sexually provocative way, clearly an imitation of DaVinci's Last Supper \\u2026  \\\"I love this: 'We tried to celebrate community tolerance.'\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2789030502669855e-28, \"text\": \"DaVinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 2257, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2541152073224375e-34, \"text\": \"Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yeah, tolerance, except for those pesky 2.6 billion Christians on the planet.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.988240008331968, \"rank\": 0.011896039909142293, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone's welcome, everyone's tolerated, all this lovely diversity until you get to anyone who disagrees with your ideology.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026  To the Paris Olympics organizing committee, not good enough.#OlympicGames#Olympics2024Paris@Olympicspic.twitter.com/p8urrYLhA0  - Bishop Robert Barron (@BishopBarron)July 28, 2024    \\\"I wonder what planet they are living on if they think that harmony and peace and all this was achieved by this clear affront to Christians,\\\" the bishop continued.\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2675, \"end\": 2688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.411508615930772e-33, \"text\": \"Robert Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\"}, {\"begin\": 2850, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.988240008331968, \"rank\": 0.011896039909142293, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Christians were offended because it was offensive, and it was intended to be offensive, so please do not patronize us with this condescending remark about, 'Well, if you had any bad feelings we are awfully sorry about that.'\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 3111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2887, \"end\": 2897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.988240008331968, \"rank\": 0.011896039909142293, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Again, if people think this so somehow gonna mollify people all over the Christian world who are outraged by what happened, I would recommend thinking again.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3185, \"end\": 3194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999731036987, \"rank\": 2.6896351252331864e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A real apology would be something like, 'This was a mistake, it should never have been done and we are sorry for it.'\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3389, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think Christians should be mollified.\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3405, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.988240008331968, \"rank\": 0.011896039909142293, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think we should keep raising our voices.\\\"\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3480, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"@BretWeinsteinis absolutely correct.\", \"from\": 3483, \"to\": 3519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics shifted the blame for their grotesque opening ceremony onto the millions who found it offensive.\", \"from\": 3520, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meaningless platitudes meant to shut down the conversation with no remorse at all.#OlympicGameshttps://t.co/aYU2SiSckn  - WorldNetDaily (@worldnetdaily)July 28, 2024    The Olympic imagery included an obese woman with a halo-like crown representing Jesus Christ in his final meal with His apostles, who were portrayed by drag queens and gay icons.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3879, \"end\": 3891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 4.219245231829294e-12, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also appearing was a scantily clad blue man with a headdress of fruit, intended to be Dionysus, the Greek god of fertility, wine and revelry.\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 4120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4065, \"end\": 4073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.297896003868375e-28, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 4079, \"end\": 4084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9967438036197467, \"rank\": 0.003262938780669723, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening of the Olympics in France recreated the Last Supper with an overweight woman as Jesus, a naked man painted blue, drag queens, and a child as disciples.\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4153, \"end\": 4159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996353252450061, \"rank\": 0.0002932608235143861, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4214, \"end\": 4219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.181876486457049e-12, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why is it acceptable to mock Christianity?\", \"from\": 4286, \"to\": 4328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4315, \"end\": 4327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9986940320890236, \"rank\": 0.0013076756933800497, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And why is it suddenly the in thing to do?\", \"from\": 4329, \"to\": 4371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"pic.twitter.com/qiP